Interface IResourceVisitor


  • public interface IResourceVisitor
    Defines the interface for a resource visitor called by the tree walker.

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean visitResource(IResourceVisitor.Resource resource, String pathName)
      This method is called by IResource.walkTree(IResourceVisitor) for both folder and non-folder resources encountered while walking the folder tree rooted at resource that walkTree was called on.

    • Method Detail

      • visitResource

        boolean visitResource(IResourceVisitor.Resource resource,
                    String pathName)
                      throws IOException
        This method is called by IResource.walkTree(IResourceVisitor) for both folder and non-folder resources encountered while walking the folder tree rooted at resource that walkTree was called on.
        Parameters:
        resource - The non-folder resource being visited.
        pathName - The path name of this resource relative to the location of the resource that walkTree was called on.
        Returns:
        True if the resource is a folder resource and the treeWalker should recurse into the folder.
        Throws:
        IOException
